abstract:
This article presents machine learning (ML)-based empirical research with a specific focus on&#13;
the financial competitiveness of different industrial sectors in Visegrad Four (V4) countries.&#13;
Financial is measured by the two most widely applied profitability ratios:&#13;
return on assets (ROA) and return equity (ROE). Several sectoral average ratios&#13;
are considered as input variables from 4 countries 27 sectors, data collected&#13;
between 2016-2020 cross-sectional approach. Explorative analysis reveals that three&#13;
strongest clustering features V4 sector-level are found country classification,&#13;
total per employee, gross margin ratios. Hypothesis examination has justified view&#13;
that drivers not necessarily identical to factors explaining&#13;
variance between Six methods have been develop&#13;
predictive models for ROA ROE. Results demonstrate traditional generalized linear&#13;
model (GENLIN) delivers insufficient predictive power despite fulfilment each statistical&#13;
assumption. The k-nearest neighbor (KNN) random forest (RF) demonstrated&#13;
to be best ML techniques predict companies.&#13;
Beyond classification, predictors ROE at level&#13;
are income margin, turnover, leverage ratios compressed components use&#13;
of principal component (PCA). also provides added value literature on&#13;
sectoral research, companies,&#13;
and efficient application methods.

